@shukriramlee  The Singapore government will raise the Local Qualifying Salary (LQS) for businesses to $1,600 starting July 1, up from the current $1,400.

Deputy Prime Minister Lawrence Wong said in his Budget 2024 speech this month that the minimum hourly rate of full-time workers will be hiked from $9 to $10.50 an hour.

"This increase ensures we keep pace with wage growth," Wong said in his speech.

@peanutsharky  yes, we buy lower grade oil, but we also sell high grade oil, that's y subsidy is reasonable as an oil country. why u only compare singapore and philipine? compare vietnam and indonesia too, their oil price is cheaper compare to our "un-subsidised rate"RM4.020 as today, gov said very burden oh(viet-RM3.563, indonesia-RM2.856 today) & they're all not oil producing country. 
stop giving false info as excuse, the "managed float" was implemented at dec 2014, and usd/myr spike from 2015 around 3.4 all the way to 4.4 the next year, and been averaging at 4.2 for many years. oil price do fall below $50 around 2016, but also climb back close to $100 at 2018, averaging  around $75, yet no above RM3/L. Now it's only 1 month plus the iran war, price above $100 only last for 2 weeks+, we can already hear talk about gov wan to abolish the subsidy.
my point is not about najib, i don't like him either, he is gone & will pay for what he did. Now, this gov is even worse, using the belief of "brainless fan" doing terrible things like broaden SST & rate, e-invoice etc. we're oil country, paying expensive oil is unreasonable. I'm just trying to shut those "brainless fans" mouth who tried to reasonate the removal of subsidy, news spread out as a test, if everyone reasonate it, it could happen maybe by reducing the quota, but I can also certainly tell u gov now don't dare to remove the oil subsidy completely as per lesson from badawi. All these "removed subsidy"are likely end up in GLC, cronies, politician & their friends pocket. Tht's the main point

@herlinawati1709 Malaysia jual sedikit komoditas tapi yg nilainya mahal dan mengimpor komoditas lain lebih banyak tapi nilainya kecil. Saudi Arabia juga hanya jual minyak dan yg lainnya mereka beli dari luar negeri. Kemandirian itu bukan tentang kita punya apa, tapi kita bisa beli apa atau tidak. 
Singapura hampir mendatangkan segalanya dari luar negeri tapi mereka pasti sanggup membelinya karena dompet mereka sangat besar dan dalam.
Dan kalo membandingkan dompet siapa yang lebih tebal antara Indonesia dan Malaysia, jelas orang  Malaysia punya dompet 2,5 x lebih tebal dari kita.
